description: This scramble offers nice views and is great early season training for bigger scrambles later on. Scramble: Class 1 ? Steep Hiking Altitude: 2,408m (7,898 ft)Elevation Gain: 700m (2,296 ft)Ascent Time: 2 HoursBest Season to Scramble: Mid-May to October
directions: From the parking lot head straight across the road, up the hill and cross over the canal. At this point you will see a small wooden building. The trailhead starts just behind the building. Once on the trail just head on up. When you reach tree line the trail traverses far over to the right side of the slope then traverses back to the summit.
title: Ha Ling Peak
